This paper proposes a new approach for training a generator model to generate data, which is relevant to the sub-fields of machine learning and computer vision. The paper discusses the advantages of the proposed method over existing approaches, such as avoiding mode collapsing and efficiently learning data manifold representation in an unsupervised manner. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of the proposed method on real-world datasets, which suggests relevance to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
